s and open interest imbalances between long and short positions. The funding mechanism adjusts based on the difference between perpetual and spot prices, with rates typically ranging from -0.01% to 0.01% per hour. Unlike order book exchanges, GMX's oracle dependency means funding rates respond to broader market sentiment rather than exchange-specific trading pressure. The GLP/GM liquidity pools provide counterparty liquidity, affecting funding calculation dynamics."}]]}],"$Lf",["$L10","$L11","$L12"],"$L13"]}],"$L14"]}]]}]
